"n.服装；剧装 【英】 n. 服装 (dress including accessories)；剧装 (a set of clothes worn in a play or at a masquerade) 【记】 来自(custom 习俗)，按习俗要求穿 的服装(put on costume according to custom) ，分割记忆：cost(花 费)＋ume,花钱的东西 →服装 【例】 actors in policemen's costumes n. 服饰(包括衣服、装饰和发型); (在狂欢节、万圣节、戏剧或化妆舞会上穿的)剧装和节日服装 【记】custom(n 习惯; 风俗); costume就是能表明某一国家、时期或民众的特点的服装. cost花费, 需要花钱的东西－服装 【记】源自custom 风俗,按习俗穿的服装；cost 花费 + me→花我老多钱的东西→(女友的)服装 costume (n.)  1715, ""style of dress,"" an art term, from French costume (17c.), from Italian costume ""fashion, habit,"" from Latin consuetudinem (nominative consuetudo) ""custom, habit, usage."" Essentially the same word as custom but arriving by a different etymology. From ""customary clothes of the particular period in which the scene is laid,"" meaning broadened by 1818 to ""any defined mode of dress."" Costume jewelry is first attested 1933. costume (v.)  1823, from costume (n.). Related: Costumed; costuming."
